@model IEnumerable<Author>

@{
    ViewBag.Title = "title";
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

<h2>List of authors</h2>

<p>This model of this view is <i>IEnumerable&lt;Author&gt;</i>. The controller must send a list of authors, which are
    then used in a foreach loop below to show each author using HTML. Mixing C# and HTML like this is what Razor
    scripting is.</p>

<p>The data is put into a Bootstrap table, which is then enhanced with the DataTables library to get sorting etc.
    This library is loaded in the layout and enabled on the table using the <i>@@section</i> syntax in the view.</p>

<p>See the <a href="https://datatables.net/examples/styling/bootstrap4">documentation</a> for how to configure the DataTables libary.</p>

<table id="authors" class="table table-striped table-bordered">
    <thead>
        <tr><th>First name</th><th>Last name</th><th>Birth date</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>

    @foreach (var author in Model)
    {
        <tr>
            <td>@author.FirstName</td><td>@author.LastName</td><td>@author.Birthdate</td>
        </tr>
    }

    </tbody>
</table>

@section Scripts {
    <script>
    $(document).ready(function() {
        $('#authors').DataTable();
    });
    </script>
}